Introduction¶

Analysis consists of exploring a dataset containing 100k medial appointments from the 
Brazilian health system and is focused on whether or not patients show up for their appointments.
Below are the variables used in dataset and analysis will be done with these data:

PatientId: Id of a patient

AppointmentID: Id of each appointment

Gender: Male or Female

ScheduledDay: The day appointment is registered.

AppointmentDay: The day of the actuall appointment

Age: Age of patient

Neighbourhood: Where the appointment hospital located

Scholarship: 0 or 1, indicates if the patient is in Healthcare program

Hipertension: 0 or 1

Diabetes: 1 or 1

Alcoholism: 1 or 1

Handcap: 0 or more

SMS_received: 0 or 1

No-show No indicates if the patient showed up to their appointment and Yes if they didn't show up

Initial analysis¶

 * There are total 110527 rows and 14 columns
 * No of rows remains same for all columns, so no missing values are seen.
 * ScheduledDay and AppointmentDay is in string format which needs to be changed to date time format
 * PatientID is duplicated, as same person has booked multiple appointments

Data Wrangling¶

In this section, data will be checked for cleanliness, dealing missing values.

Following tasks are performed
    1. Renaming columns to standard format
    2. Identifying the columns that require data type conversion
    3. Dropping the columns having null values
    4. Checking for duplicates
    5. Checking whether data needs to be categorized for detailed analysis

In [1993]:
# Method to plot using seaborn plot for no_show rate
# dataset : current dataset
# feature : feature against which no_show_rate is plotted
# xlabel : label name of the feature
# fsize : font size required for plotting
# additional_plot_status : Adding extra parameters to plot for better visualization

def feature_no_show_plot(dataset,feature,xlabel,fsize, additional_plot_status):
    no_show = sns.countplot(x= feature,hue='no_show',data=dataset)
    no_show.set_xlabel(xlabel,fontsize = fsize)
    no_show.set_ylabel("No of patients",fontsize = fsize)
    
    if additional_plot_status == True:
        no_show.tick_params(labelsize = 20)
        no_show.set_xticklabels(no_show.get_xticklabels(),rotation=90)
        plt.legend(fontsize=20)
    
    plt.title('Appointment show up based on '+xlabel, fontsize = fsize)
    plt.show()
In [1994]:
# Method to plot percentage distribution of various datapoints using pie chart

def feature_percentage_distribution_no_show(percent,values,colors,explode,feature, fsize):
    plt.pie(percent, colors=colors, labels=values, explode=explode ,startangle=90, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title("Appointment show up by "+feature , fontsize=12)
    plt.show()

## Find no of males who has not shown up for appointments
male_count_show = df.query('gender == "M" and no_show == 1').no_show.count()

# Find no of femails who has not shown up for appointments
female_count_show = df.query('gender == "F" and no_show == 1').no_show.count()
total_show = df.query('no_show == 1').no_show.count()

female_show_percentage = female_count_show/total_show *100
male_show_percentage = male_count_show / total_show * 100

print("Percentage of women who turn up for appointment :",round(female_show_percentage,2))
print("Percentage of men who turn up for appointment :", round(male_show_percentage,2))

percent = [male_show_percentage,female_show_percentage]
values = ['Male','Female']

explode = [0,0.1]
colors = ['cyan','teal']

feature_percentage_distribution_no_show(percent,values,colors,explode,"Gender", 12)

Conclusion¶

From the above dataset analysis, factors that can be thought of having impact on appointment show up

1. Age group as more than half of turned up patients belongs to elderly category ( > 37 yrs)
2. Wait days - As the wait days increases, show up for appointment rate decreases. 
   Higher turn up when the appointment is on same day
3. Gender- Female patients are having higher show up compared to male.
4. Patients who doesn't have any medical conditions turn up for appointments more.
5. Health program enrollment has no impact has 90% of patients turned up didnt had any.
6. Most of patients turned up for appointments are from `Jardim Camburi` neighbourhood.
